            <td align="left" valign="top"><!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="Content" --><p><a href="../index.html">Club Penguin Help</a> &gt; <a href="../technical_help.html">Technical Help</a> &gt; Some parts of the game aren&rsquo;t appearing on my screen?</p>
                <h1>Some parts of the game aren&rsquo;t appearing on my screen? </h1>
              <p>There are two main reasons why this could be happening:</p>
              <ol>
                <li><strong>Reason 1 - Screen Resolution
                  </strong><br>
                  You might not have enough <strong><a href="glossary-technical-terms.htm#screen-res" class="iconlinks">screen resolution</a></strong> to show these parts of the game. It&rsquo;s easy to  adjust your screen resolution.<br>
                  <br>
                  <ul>
                    <li><a href="#PC" class="iconlinks">If you are using PC</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#MAC" class="iconlinks">If you are using a Mac</a><br>
                      <br>
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li><a href="#download-flash-player" class="iconlinks">Download a new flash player </a></li>
              </ol>
			  
              <p><a name="PC"></a></p>
              <h2>Reason #1:              </h2>
              <p><strong>If you are using a PC</strong>:</p>
              <table width="372" border="0" align="right" cellspacing="0">
                <tr>
                  <td align="right"><img src="images/Screen-ResWin-step1.gif" width="350" height="220"><br>
                      <img src="images/Screen-ResWin-step2.gif" width="350" height="220"></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td align="right"><p align="right"><a href="#top">back to top</a>		      </p></td>
                </tr>
              </table>
             
			  <ol>
                <li>Log  out of Club Penguin. Go to the desktop of your computer.<br>
                  <br>
                </li>
                <li>Click  on the right button on your mouse. A box will pop up. Click on &ldquo;Properties.&rdquo;<br>
                  <br>
                </li>
                <li>Another  box will pop up. Look at the tabs running across the top. Click on &ldquo;Settings.&rdquo;<br>
                  <br>
                </li>
                <li>You  will see a little box titled &ldquo;Screen Resolution.&rdquo; In this box is a bar with an  arrow on it. Use your mouse to drag the bar to the right until the screen  resolution reads 1024 by 768 pixels or higher.<br>
                  <br>
</li>
                <li>Click  &ldquo;OK.&rdquo;<br>
                  <br>
                </li>
                <li>Log  back on to Club Penguin and try playing the game again.</li>
              </ol>
			  <p>&nbsp;</p>
			  <p>&nbsp;</p>
			  <p>&nbsp;</p>
			  <p>&nbsp;</p>
			  <p>&nbsp;</p>
			  
			  <table width="372" border="0" align="right" cellspacing="0">
                <tr>
                  <td align="right"><img src="images/Screen-ResMac-step1.gif" width="350" height="220"><br>
                  <img src="images/Screen-ResMac-step2.gif" width="350" height="220"></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td align="right"><p align="right"><a href="#top">back to top</a></p></td>
                </tr>
              </table>
			  <a name="MAC"></a><p><strong>If you are using a Mac</strong>:</p>
              <ol>
                <li>Log  out of Club Penguin.<br>
                  <br>
                </li>
                <li>Click  on the blue apple icon on the top left of your screen. A menu will appear.  Click on &ldquo;System Preferences.&rdquo;<br>
                  <br>
                </li>
                <li>Find  the icon that looks like a computer monitor. It will say &ldquo;Display&rdquo; underneath.  Click on this icon.<br>
                  <br>
                </li>
                <li>A  box will pop up. Inside this box you will see the word &ldquo;Resolutions.&rdquo; Make sure  that the resolution highlighted is &ldquo;1024 x 768&rdquo; or higher. If it is not, use  your mouse to highlight &ldquo;1024 x 768.&rdquo;<br>
                  <br>
                </li>
                <li>Click  on the red button on the top of the box to close the box.<br>  
                  <br>
                </li>
                <li>
                  Log  back on to Club Penguin and try playing the game again.                </li>
              </ol>
			  <p>&nbsp;</p>
			  <p>&nbsp;</p>
               <p>&nbsp;</p> 
			   <p>&nbsp;</p>  
			  <a name="download-flash-player"></a><h2>Reason #2:              </h2>
              <p>You might not have the right version of Adobe Flash  Player to run the game properly.&nbsp; You  will need to download a new <a href="glossary-technical-terms.htm#flash-player" class="iconlinks">flash  player</a>. There are a few ways to do this;</p>
              <ol>
                <li>Try  to play a game on Club Penguin. You may get a message that says you need to  download the newest version of Flash Player. Don&rsquo;t ignore it. Click &ldquo;OK&rdquo; to  start and follow the steps you are given.<br>
                  <br>
</li>
                <li>Visit <a href="http://www.macromedia.com/go/getflashplayer/" target="_blank" class="iconlinks">Flash Player Download Center</a> to  update Flash Player.  Follow the instructions on the Adobe website.</li>
              </ol>
              <p align="right"><a href="#top">back to top</a> </p>
            <!-- InstanceEndEditable --></td>
          </tr>
        </table>
	  </td>
    </tr>
